  "text": "Hamster sperm were obtained from adult male epididymides by swim-out in sperm washing medium [SWM: 72 mM NaCl, 1.5 mM KCl, 3.2 mM Na 2 HPO 4 , 0.6 mM KH 2 PO 4 , 0.5 mM CaCl 2 , 0.4 mM MgCl 2 , 150 mM sucrose and 1 mg/ml of polyvinyl alcohol (PVA)] and purification through a glass bead column as described previously [CITATION_1] . Sperm were incubated under capacitating conditions using TL medium (101.02 mM NaCl, 2.68 mM KCl, 1.8 mM CaCl 2 , 0.5 mM MgCl 2 , 35.7 mM NaHCO 3 , 0.35 mM NaH 2 PO 4 , 9 mM sodium lactate, 4.5 mM glucose and 1 mg/ml of PVA), supplemented with 0.25 mM sodium pyruvate, 3 mg/ml of fatty-acid-free BSA and motility factors (2 mM D-penicillamine, 10 mM hypotaurine and 100 uM epinephrine) (Tyrode's albumin lactate pyruvate medium, TALP; [CITATION_2] . Alternatively, a modified TALP was prepared replacing CaCl 2 with SrCl 2 (TALP-Sr). Medium (0.5 ml/well) was placed in 24-well dishes (Costar, Corning, Acton, MA, USA), covered with mineral oil and equilibrated for 1 h at 378C in a 5% CO 2 atmosphere. Aliquots of the purified sperm suspension were added to each well (5 × 10 5 cells/ml) and incubated for a total period of 6 h. AR of at least 100 motile cells was evaluated by light microscopy (dark field, 200×) [CITATION_3] . Aliquots were also taken for objective motility evaluation by light microscopy. No effect on motility was evident for any of the agents tested. To analyze their effect on AR, agents were added to wells at the end of the capacitation period (3 h of incubation) and AR evaluated 30 min later and/or at final incubation time (6 h).",
